Q17: Just a small suggestion but it might be helpful to directly host the robot videos on Qualtrics rather than have them embedded in the study via YouTube. I frequently paused and rewatched the videos to ensure that I didn't miss anything and every time that happens on YouTube, a banner pops up with suggested videos. It gets repetitive to manually dismiss that suggested video banner again and again in order to see the map. I think all browsers nowadays can play .mp4s directly in them and so it could be useful to bypass hosting videos on YouTube entirely. Additionally, the video compression (likely the result of YouTube) made it a bit hard to discern between the yellow and green objects. The green ended up a bit too yellow-green. Perhaps a more contrasting color like magenta could be used.
